cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "Machine-Speed Cyber and Poisoned Cognition: A Layer-Dependent Game-Theoretic Framework, with Empirical Probes"
abstract: >-
  A framework paper with first-pass empirical probes arguing that AI-mediated conflict is a
  layered strategic environment (wire / model-weights / audit / attribution), formalized with
  five compact model results and seven falsifiable predictions, with wire-layer clustering and
  model-layer capture-bound probes grounded on open data.
type: report
